  "text": "Some measurement that is useful in this field is correctly read words per minute(CWPM) [CITATION_1] and relative number of correctly read words (REL_ CW). CWPM is a widely used measure for oral reading proficiencyand is computed by subtracting deletion and substitution errors from the reference text and then dividing the result by the reading time in minutes. After the student reading the comprehension then the actual time is recorded and the silence time is computed by using zero crossing method:",
